						<summary>

						<p>Near the foot-prints engraved on the hill.</p>						

						<p>This epigraph engraved in characters of about the 14th century A.D., records that the foot-prints of Śrī Sakasāṉandar (i.e., śrī Sahajānanda) were caused to be carved by a certain Avaiyampukkāṉ.</p>						

